td.paragraph: For
her ongoing bilateral lower extremity heaviness, aching, restlessness, and
swelling, which is worse in her right lower extremity despite compression
stocking therapy during the day for over six months without significant symptom
relief and known venous insufficiency, we will arrange for RGSV venous ablation
on today's visit. Risks, benefits, and alternatives were discussed in great
detail. We provided the patient with information and educational material on
venous ablation therapy and venous insufficiency. She tolerated the procedure
well. We advised her to continue compliance with compression stocking therapy
during the day and resting and elevating her legs at night. We also discussed
the fact that the long-term side-effects of Wegovy are not well-known and that
she needs to maintain an ongoing caloric deficit for optimal weight reduction.
All questions and concerns were answered and addressed and a heart-healthy diet
and healthy lifestyle was encouraged and endorsed. She will follow-up in 1 week
or sooner should symptoms arise. She agrees to the plan of care.
Provided education on diet modifications, proper food choices, nutritional counseling and review of diet journal.

tr.td: Scribed by Devendra Bisht under the supervision of Dr. Rishi Bajaj and Daliah Rodriguez, MS

All questions and concerns were answered and addressed. We advise her to continue using her compression socks during the day, rest and elevate her legs at night. She will follow-up on Sunday in Monticello or sooner if symptoms arise. She agrees to the plan of care.
Scribed by Mohd Irshad under the supervision of Dr. Rishi Bajaj and Daliah Rodriguez, MS

td.paragraph: For
her ongoing lower extremity heaviness, aching, swelling, itching and burning at
the sites of bulging varicosities despite CTT for over 6 months and known
venous insufficiency, we will arrange for LSSV ablation on today's visit.
Risks, benefits, and alternatives were discussed in great detail. All questions and concerns were answered and
addressed. Heart healthy diet and healthy lifestyle encouraged and endorsed.
She tolerated the procedure well. She will follow up in 1 week or sooner should
symptoms worsen. She agrees to the plan of care

tr.td: Scribed by Shashank Kapoor under the supervision of Dr. Rishi Bajaj and Daliah Rodriguez, MS

td.paragraph: For her complaints of lightheadedness and dizziness, we will arrange for a carotid doppler at her next visit. For her complaints of BLE numbness tingling, and cramping, we will arrange for an ABI/PVR which revealed RLE 0.79 and LLE 0.54. We will arrange for a BLE arterial doppler for her numbness tingling, cramping, and abnormal ABI/PVR at her next visit. For her BLE heaviness, aching, swelling, throbbing discomfort, we will arrange for a venous reflux exam. Preliminary images reviewed and discussed which revealed significant venous reflux in bilateral lower extremities. We provided educational material on venous insufficiency and treatment with venous ablation therapy. We advised her continuing compliance with compression stocking therapy during the day, resting and elevating her legs at night for ongoing management of her BLE heaviness and swelling discomfort. All questions and concerns were answered and addressed. Heart healthy diet and healthy lifestyle encouraged and endorsed. She will follow up on Tuesday in Liberty or sooner should symptoms worsen. She agrees with the plan of care.

Time Spent: Total time spent 85 minutes in face-to-face conversation, examination, reviewing records, discussing treatment options and procedures, pathophysiology, and anatomy. Diet and lifestyle modifications were discussed in great detail. Images were personally reviewed by me in front of the patient and/or family member and explained on our graphic diagram. Treatment options, risks, benefits and alternative treatments discussed with the patient in detail. All questions and concerns answered.

out any temporal arteritis. Preliminary results reviewed and discussed with
patient that were negative for any inflammation. For her recent LSSV ablation,
we will obtain a post venous doppler. Preliminary results reviewed and
discussed with patient, are negative for DVT. Her SSV is closed. We will plan
on RSSV ablation at her next visit. All questions and concerns answered and
addressed. Heart healthy diet and lifestyle encouraged and endorsed. We will
see her back in one to two weeks for RSSV ablation. She agrees with plan of care.

td.paragraph: A
post-procedure venous ultrasound done today was negative for DVTs.
Physical exam revealed bilateral 2+ pitting edema, right greater than
left, but no pain or bruising. Pedal pulses were intact. The patient
will continue compression therapy and leg elevation as tolerated. We
reassured her based on negative post-procedure duplex ultrasound
findings. We advised monitoring for any new or worsening symptoms
such as redness, worsening swelling, or signs of infection. A
follow-up visit is scheduled for 07/27 to continue cardiovascular
evaluation and assess for further interventions. All questions and
concerns answered and addressed. Heart healthy diet and healthy
lifestyle modifications were encouraged and endorsed. Patient
expressed understanding and agreed with the management plan.

tr.td: Scribed by Devendra Bisht under the supervision of Dr. Rishi Bajaj and Shellene Napier, NP

For post-ablation evaluation, we will arrange for BLE venous doppler on today's visit. Preliminary images were reviewed and discussed which revealed no evidence of DVT. Given her persistent lower extremity heaviness and swelling, we will arrange for a venous reflux exam at her next visit for evaluation of possible ongoing below-the-knee reflux. All questions and concerns were answered and addressed. A heart-healthy diet and healthy lifestyle were encouraged and endorsed. She was encouraged to continue wearing compression socks during the day, rest and elevate her legs at night. She will follow-up in 1-2 weeks or sooner if symptoms arise. She agrees to the plan of care.
Scribed by Sushil Rai under the supervision of Dr. Rishi Bajaj and Daliah Rodriguez, MS

Due to the patient's complaints of continued bulging, heaviness, swelling, pain, and burning at the site of bulging varicosities, we arranged to complete a venous reflux study. Preliminary images were reviewed with the patient at great length, which displayed significant reflux bilaterally, but no evidence of DVTs. Due to this, the patient was encouraged to continue compliance with compression stocking therapy during the day, resting and elevating of her legs at night. The patient was also given educational material regarding venous reflux and below-the-knee venous ablation therapy. We are currently pending authorization for below-the-knee venous ablation therapy bilaterally. Once we will obtain authorization for below-the-knee venous ablation therapy, we plan to schedule the ablation. All questions and concerns were answered and addressed. A heart-healthy diet and healthy lifestyle were encouraged and endorsed. She is to follow up in two weeks or sooner should symptoms arise. She agrees with the plan of care.
Scribed by Intekhab Alam and Madison Luxmore under the supervision of Dr. Rishi Bajaj

td.paragraph: This is an 80-year-old female with a significant medical history of hypertension, obesity, peripheral vascular disease, hyperlipidemia, and gastroesophageal reflux disease, who presents today for a cardiovascular follow-up for leg discomfort. She has ongoing heaviness, aching, restlessness, throbbing, and swelling in her bilateral lower extremities. She reports compliance with compression stocking therapy during the day and resting and elevating her legs at night for over six months without significant symptom relief. She is a retired dairy farmer and reports that she spent a significant amount of time on her feet. She is currently status post cardiac catheterization from December 2024 by Dr. Mercado at Crystal Run. She reports to be following up with him. She recently had an echocardiogram completed at an outside facility by Dr. Mercardo. She was recently started on Wegovy which is being managed by her PCP and reports to be tolerating it well. She denies any nausea, constipation, or other abdominal discomfort. She reports bilateral lower extremity swelling which is worse in her right lower extremity. She denies any active chest pain, chest pressure, syncope, or near-syncopal events.
ABI/PVR: RLE 0.79, LLE 0.54.
Venous reflux: Significant venous reflux in bilateral lower extremities.

For her ongoing bilateral lower extremity heaviness, aching, restlessness, and swelling, which is worse in her right lower extremity despite compression stocking therapy during the day for over six months without significant symptom relief and known venous insufficiency, we will arrange for RGSV venous ablation on today's visit. Risks, benefits, and alternatives were discussed in great detail. We provided the patient with information and educational material on venous ablation therapy and venous insufficiency. She tolerated the procedure well. We advised her to continue compliance with compression stocking therapy during the day and resting and elevating her legs at night. We also discussed the fact that the long-term side-effects of Wegovy are not well-known and that she needs to maintain an ongoing caloric deficit for optimal weight reduction.
